The antenna is analyzed in receiving mode, mainly for EM field sensor. The performance of the EM field sensor is predicted in terms of complex antenna factor (CAF) or antenna factor (AF) for time domain or frequency domain measurement respectively. To analyze of an antenna in receiving mode, the antenna is be illuminated by a plane wave. Due to the incidence of EM field, current is induced on the antenna and resulting voltage $(V_{50}(\omega))$ at the measuring device of 50 $\Omega$ input impedance is developed. FDTD is used to calculate this voltage $V_{50}(\omega)$. CAF which is the complex ratio between incident electric field $E_i(\omega)$ and the measured voltage $V_{50}(\omega)$ is next calculated \cite{Shinobu_Near_Field_3_Antenna_Method}. The conventional AF is simply the CAF without phase information and is therefore also available.
